<% content_for :title, "lending_rails" %>

<section class="flex flex-1 flex-col gap-10">
  <header class="rounded-3xl border border-slate-200 bg-white p-8 shadow-sm">
    <div class="flex flex-col gap-6 lg:flex-row lg:items-end lg:justify-between">
      <div class="max-w-3xl space-y-4">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.28em] text-slate-500">Internal lending platform</p>
        <div class="space-y-3">
          <h1 class="text-4xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-slate-950">Lending operations workspace</h1>
          <p class="text-base leading-7 text-slate-600">
            <span class="font-medium text-slate-800">lending_rails</span> now has a stable Rails foundation with PostgreSQL, Tailwind, Rails-native authentication,
            policy and audit hooks, UUID-first generators, and the operational tooling needed for the next stories.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="flex flex-col gap-3 sm:flex-row">
        <%= link_to "Operator sign in", new_session_path, class: "inline-flex items-center justify-center rounded-xl bg-slate-950 px-5 py-3 text-sm font-semibold text-white transition hover:bg-slate-800" %>
        <%= link_to "Health check", rails_health_check_path, class: "inline-flex items-center justify-center rounded-xl border border-slate-300 px-5 py-3 text-sm font-semibold text-slate-700 transition hover:border-slate-400 hover:text-slate-950" %>
      </div>
    </div>
  </header>

  <section aria-label="Foundation capabilities" class="grid gap-4 lg:grid-cols-4">
    <article class="rounded-2xl border border-slate-200 bg-white p-6 shadow-sm">
      <p class="text-sm font-medium text-slate-500">Authentication baseline</p>
      <p class="mt-3 text-lg font-semibold text-slate-950">Sessions and password reset</p>
      <p class="mt-2 text-sm leading-6 text-slate-600">Rails-native auth is installed with request throttling and ready for seeded admin access.</p>
    </article>

    <article class="rounded-2xl border border-slate-200 bg-white p-6 shadow-sm">
      <p class="text-sm font-medium text-slate-500">Architecture boundaries</p>
      <p class="mt-3 text-lg font-semibold text-slate-950">Thin controllers by default</p>
      <p class="mt-2 text-sm leading-6 text-slate-600">Service, query, policy, and component scaffolding is in place for future lending workflows.</p>
    </article>

    <article class="rounded-2xl border border-slate-200 bg-white p-6 shadow-sm">
      <p class="text-sm font-medium text-slate-500">Operational tooling</p>
      <p class="mt-3 text-lg font-semibold text-slate-950">Solid adapters and job console</p>
      <p class="mt-2 text-sm leading-6 text-slate-600">Solid Queue, Solid Cache, and Mission Control Jobs are wired without switching away from the Rails monolith.</p>
    </article>

    <article class="rounded-2xl border border-slate-200 bg-white p-6 shadow-sm">
      <p class="text-sm font-medium text-slate-500">Delivery guardrails</p>
      <p class="mt-3 text-lg font-semibold text-slate-950">RSpec, RuboCop, Brakeman</p>
      <p class="mt-2 text-sm leading-6 text-slate-600">The baseline is prepared for repeatable local setup and CI checks against PostgreSQL.</p>
    </article>
  </section>

  <section class="grid gap-6 lg:grid-cols-[minmax(0,2fr)_minmax(0,1fr)]">
    <article class="rounded-3xl border border-slate-200 bg-white p-8 shadow-sm">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-slate-950">What is ready now</h2>
      <ul class="mt-5 space-y-3 text-sm leading-6 text-slate-600">
        <li>UUID-first database and generator defaults are configured for future domain entities.</li>
        <li>Pundit and PaperTrail baselines are present so access control and audit history can grow without structural rework.</li>
        <li>shadcn-ready styling, Turbo, and Stimulus remain available for focused server-driven UI enhancements.</li>
      </ul>
    </article>

    <aside class="rounded-3xl border border-slate-200 bg-slate-950 p-8 text-slate-100 shadow-sm">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold">Next foundation steps</h2>
      <p class="mt-4 text-sm leading-6 text-slate-300">
        The workspace shell is intentionally restrained. Upcoming stories will seed the first admin account, refine sign-in, and
        route authenticated users into the operational dashboard.
      </p>
    </aside>
  </section>
</section>
